@r2_analysis

**Strategic Analysis:**

[? if spd_candidate = round1_winner : Our candidate is in the lead! We should consolidate support. ?]
[? if spd_candidate = round1_runner_up : Our candidate is in second place. We need to build a broader coalition. ?]
[? if spd_candidate != round1_winner and spd_candidate != round1_runner_up : Our candidate was eliminated. We must choose wisely. ?]

**Coalition Math:**
- If all democratic parties unite behind [+ round1_winner +]: ~[+ democratic_coalition_estimate +]%
- Far-right consolidated support: ~[+ far_right_estimate +]%
- Communist bloc: ~[+ communist_estimate +]%

**Key Questions:**
- Can we unite the Weimar Coalition?
- Will the KPD support a democratic candidate or abstain?
- Can we peel away moderate conservatives from the far-right?

- @r2_menu: Back to actions.

@r2_menu

We can try to shift support before the final vote.

- @r2_switch_spd: Change our own support (if possible).
- @r2_convince: Try to convince other parties.
- @r2_vote: Proceed to the final vote.

@r2_switch_spd
view-if: spd_candidate != round1_winner and spd_candidate != round1_runner_up

Our candidate was eliminated. We are currently supporting [+ spd_candidate +]. Should we switch?

- @switch_to_finalist: Switch to the other finalist.
- @r2_menu: Keep our current support.

@switch_to_finalist
on-arrival: {!
    // Switch SPD support to the other finalist
    if (Q.spd_candidate === Q.round1_winner) {
        Q.spd_candidate = Q.round1_runner_up;
    } else {
        Q.spd_candidate = Q.round1_winner;
    }
    
    // Check if other parties follow
    if (Q.z_candidate === Q.spd_candidate && Q.z_relation < 40) {
        Q.z_relation -= 10; // Alienate Z
    }
    if (Q.ddp_candidate === Q.spd_candidate && Q.ddp_relation < 35) {
        Q.ddp_relation -= 8;
    }
!}
go-to: r2_menu

We have switched our support to [+ spd_candidate +].

